# Keep README.md and SPECS.md current

After any change that affects **behavior, APIs, configuration, observability, resiliency, scope, or how to run the project**, update documentation in the same turn.

## Must update when

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed endpoint, status code, or payload | `SPECS.md` contracts + `README.md` endpoint tables |
| New config flag / env var | Both docs + example in README |
| Resiliency / shutdown / retry behavior | SPECS § resiliency + README |
| Observability stack | README URLs + SPECS observability |
| In/out of scope | SPECS non-goals + `PROJECT.md` |
| New module/file of architectural significance | SPECS layout + `PROJECT.md` function index |

## Also update

- [`PROJECT.md`](PROJECT.md) — request lifecycle, feature matrix, function references
- [`E2E_TESTING_GUIDE.md`](E2E_TESTING_GUIDE.md) — only when operator walkthrough steps change

## Do not

- Skip docs because the change “is small”
- Leave SPECS contradicting code
- Add speculative features to docs that are not implemented
